# Compliance Filter (R3-Q3)

## Three-Layer Architecture

Applied before publishing. Each layer is independently testable.

```
Layer 1: HARD RULES (regex/keyword) — FREE
  ↓ pass
Layer 2: POLICY CHECKS (LLM) — costs eval tokens
  ↓ pass
Layer 3: BRAND SAFETY (LLM) — costs eval tokens
  ↓ pass
PUBLISHABLE
```

Layers 2–3 only run on ads that pass Layer 1.

## Layer 1: Regex Hard-Stops

Must catch with zero LLM cost:

| Pattern | Regex | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Dollar amounts without disclaimers | `\$\d+` | Unverified pricing |
| Competitor trademarks (negative context) | `Princeton Review\|Kaplan\|Khan Academy\|Chegg` | Disparagement |
| Absolute guarantees | `guaranteed\|100%\|always\|never fail` | Misleading claims |
| PII patterns | Email, phone, SSN regex | Data protection |

## Layer 2: LLM Policy Checks

Gemini Flash evaluates:
- No misleading claims or unverified statistics
- CTA matches funnel stage (awareness vs. conversion)
- Tone appropriate for target audience
- No fear-based language implying the child is deficient

## Layer 3: LLM Brand Safety

Gemini Flash evaluates:
- Nothing that could embarrass Varsity Tutors
- No cultural insensitivity
- No urgency that crosses into fear-mongering
- No absolute promises about outcomes

## Hard No-Go List

NEVER generate:
- "Guaranteed 1500+" or any guaranteed score improvement
- Fear-based language ("your child is falling behind")
- Specific competitor disparagement by name
- Unverified statistics, pricing, or testimonials
- "100% guaranteed", "always works", "never fail"
- PII in generated content

## Implementation

- `generate/compliance.py` owns all three layers (P2-06)
- Returns `ComplianceResult` with `passes: bool`, `violations: list`
- Every compliance check result logged in ledger
- Compliance is part of the evaluation pipeline, not a post-processing step

## Do NOT

- Skip Layer 1 because "the LLM will catch it" — regex is free and deterministic
- Run Layers 2–3 on ads that fail Layer 1 — waste of tokens
- Weaken compliance rules to increase pass rates
- Apply compliance after publishing — it's a pre-publish gate
